 <tr>
  <th scope="row">
   Known for
  </th>
  <td>
   Writing
   <i>
    Certaine Errors in Navigation
   </i>
   (1599) which first explained the mathematical basis for the
   <a href="/wiki/Mercator_projection" title="Mercator projection">
    Mercator projection
   </a>
   , producing the Wright–Molyneux map (
   <i>
    ca.
   </i>
   1599), and translating
   <a href="/wiki/John_Napier" title="John Napier">
    John Napier
   </a>
   's work on
   <a href="/wiki/Logarithm" title="Logarithm">
    logarithms
   </a>
   which was published as
   <i>
    A Description of the Admirable Table of Logarithmes
   </i>
   (1616)
  </td>
